      "id": "PopularPost96354",
      "post_content": "For people complaining that this is a broken card, let me direct you to [Ancestral Recall](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancestral Recall), which, unlike Counterspell, is a card that caused a major imbalance when it was around, hence why it will never be reprinted. With Counterspell, keep in mind that, even unlike [Doom Blade](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doom Blade) and [Lightning Bolt](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt), you have to leave your mana pool open in case your opponent does something you do not want resolving. If you see this as \"too much\" of a problem, remember that Counterspells/[Cancel](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cancel)s/[Mana Leak](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mana Leak)s/whatever can still be countered. You'd usually have to run blue in order to do this (unless you have [Dash Hopes](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dash Hopes) or something similar) but it's far from a card that will completely ruin the game. Long explanation short, Counterspell isn't any less game wrecking than a Lightning Bolt or a [Path to Exile](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Path to Exile); there are thousands of cards in Magic which, in turn, presen... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Keiya",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost96354\">\n<span id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_post\">For people complaining that this is a broken card, let me direct you to <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Ancestral Recall\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Ancestral Recall\">Ancestral Recall</a>, which, unlike Counterspell, is a card that caused a major imbalance when it was around, hence why it will never be reprinted. With Counterspell, keep in mind that, even unlike <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Doom Blade\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doom Blade\">Doom Blade</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Lightning Bolt\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Lightning Bolt\">Lightning Bolt</a>, you have to leave your mana pool open in case your opponent does something you do not want resolving. If you see this as \"too much\" of a problem, remember that Counterspells/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Cancel\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cancel\">Cancel</a>s/<a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mana Leak\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mana Leak\">Mana Leak</a>s/whatever can still be countered. You'd usually have to run blue in order to do this (unless you have <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Dash Hopes\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dash Hopes\">Dash Hopes</a> or something similar) but it's far from a card that will completely ruin the game. Long explanation short, Counterspell isn't any less game wrecking than a Lightning Bolt or a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Path to Exile\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Path to Exile\">Path to Exile</a>; there are thousands of cards in Magic which, in turn, presen... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 96354)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_post